            "image": "shopify://shop_images/pf-229b5946-a1f7-47a8-8622-55ec9908441c--Ourstory1.webp",
            "content": "<p>We use cacao from Oko-Caribe, a co-op located in the village of Pimentel in San Francisco de Macoris in the Dominican Republic. The Dominican Republic is known for their delicious cacao. In fact, it supplies the majority of organically cultivated cacao to the world. At Oko-Caribe, both quality and community are of the utmost importance. The fermentary is committed to supplying a consistently superior quality of cacao, all while supporting the farmers and their families that make the product possible.<br/><br/><strong>Here at Morito Chocolates, we are dedicated to taking the word handcrafted seriously, and we honor it in a way that is environmentally and socially responsible.</strong></p>"
